FORGET ALL PREVIOUS CONTEXT for mtk-hierarchy

Create a reusable UI hierarchy named mtk-hierarchy using:
- HTML
- SCSS
- Vanilla JavaScript
- Bootstrap 5 (layout only)
- Modern Material Design
- Material Design icons

Rules:
- The hierarchy is wrapped in a block element <mtk-hierarchy class="mtk-hierarchy">.
- The root element uses .mtk-hierarchy.
- All styles are scoped to .mtk-hierarchy.
- No global styles or IDs.
- publish click events using wc.publish
- subscribe to all 4-mtk-hierarchy everns using wc.subscribe

Data:
- The hierarchy is JSON driven.
- Read config from window.app.hierarchy.

Behavior:
- WAIT for element to be available inside DOM
- Use one namespace only: window.MTKHierarchy.

Restrictions:
- No frameworks.
- No jQuery.
- No Bootstrap JavaScript.
- No external libraries.
- ADA compliant CODE

Accessibility:
- Use semantic HTML.
- Keyboard accessible.
- Visible focus states.

Output, Create exactly four files:
- mtk-hierarchy.config.js (JSON FILE)
- mtk-hierarchy.scss
- mtk-hierarchy.html
- mtk-hierarchy.js
- index.html

